": "http://www.jvanderspek.com/DEV/RenderTools", "icon_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/icon", "labels": ["OpenGL Scenegraph"], "moved_to_url": "", "name": "RenderTools", "preferred_support_tool": "discussion", "preferred_support_url": "", "private": false, "screenshots": [{"caption": "StyleClash is the first game that uses RenderTools", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/screenshot/styleclashmachine1square.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/screenshot/styleclashmachine1square.png"}, {"caption": "StyleClash is the first game that uses RenderTools", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/screenshot/styleclashmachine2square.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/screenshot/styleclashmachine2square.png"}, {"caption": "StyleClash is the first game that uses RenderTools", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/screenshot/styleclashmachine1square.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/rendertools/screenshot/styleclashmachine1square.png"}], "short_description": "RenderTools is an OpenGL based scenegraph library in C++ for Windows, OSX and IOS supporting OpenGL|ES1.1, ES2.0, OpenGL1.5 and up to the latest version (currently 4.2). It allows the developer to easily (de)serialize a scenegraph to-and-from xml, create renderbuffers, framebuffers, samplers, vertexbuffers etc. and cross-reference those items.  RenderTools allows you to completely specify an application, its resources, viewcontrollers and its renderpasses in one single xml. GraphNodes such as RelationalNode, RenderNode, and TransformNode can be used to create a complex hierarchy for rendering. Both update and render calls can selectively include or exclude specific components such as geometric details or lighting or texturing. ", "shortname": "rendertools", "socialnetworks": [], "status": "active", "summary": "A cross-platform OpenGL based lightweight scenegraph library ", "tools": [{"label": "Files", "mount